Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.43,0:00:18.40,Lucy-Song-Title,,0,0,0,,[I want to be a rainbow]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.68,0:00:29.86,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa hoshifuru yoru ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.11,0:00:36.79,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono tomoshibi wo keshi wa shinai to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.07,0:00:47.92,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa akane no asa ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.17,0:00:56.85,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wakaba ni somaru haru wo yobou to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.13,0:01:08.74,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Ono utsu hibiki michi hiraku utagoe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.02,0:01:20.63,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kodama ga mune ni hazunde kuru no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.91,0:01:26.47,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono oosora no niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:36.27,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kibou ni todoku niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.68,0:00:29.86,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow I made on that starry night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.11,0:00:36.79,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To not let this flame die
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.07,0:00:47.92,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow made on that brilliant red morning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.17,0:00:56.85,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To call out for spring, dyed with young leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.13,0:01:08.74,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,Cutting axes open up roads, under the sound of singing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.02,0:01:20.63,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,The echoes bounce around in my chest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.91,0:01:26.47,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow in this big sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:36.27,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow that reaches out to hope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.60,0:01:53.52,Lucy-Ep-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,306.667)\fade(100,110)}Ep. 19 - Today is the Shopping Day
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.80,0:01:59.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.91,0:02:02.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sis, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.42,0:02:05.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever it is, do it quicker, sis!\NQuicker, quicker!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.70,0:02:09.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I jotted down everything we need there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.99,0:02:13.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see. But if the prices turn out to be\Nway above the expectations, what do I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.78,0:02:15.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be in trouble, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.23,0:02:18.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But even if it's expensive,\Nwe can't do without buying those.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.43,0:02:20.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Those are all the absolute necessities.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.64,0:02:23.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sis! What's all that dawdling around?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.71,0:02:27.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Would you look at how happy those two are\Nto finally go shopping again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.10,0:02:30.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They got so excited just from learning\Nabout the town's market district. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.89,0:02:33.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You call it market district,\Nbut really it's just three shops. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.80,0:02:35.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, hurry up now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.39,0:02:39.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Getting to Carrington Street takes quite a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.13,0:02:41.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you do it at leisure,\Nyou'll only be back in the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.72,0:02:43.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I have those two to rely on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.44,0:02:46.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hope we'll still be able to walk fast,\Neven with our bags full. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.29,0:02:49.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, make haste, sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.94,0:02:51.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Wait! Wait! Why the rush?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.94,0:02:55.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What more reason you need\Nother than going shopping sooner?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.11,0:02:59.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Listen now. I understand you may be a little excited\Nabout this, but it's not a reason to lose head. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.51,0:03:00.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.68,0:03:02.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And you need to listen carefully to what I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.90,0:03:03.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We will.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.09,0:03:05.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good. With that, we can go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.08,0:03:07.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Clara.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.20,0:03:09.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Will you do me a favor?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.57,0:03:10.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.08,0:03:14.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,See you later, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.88,0:03:16.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,'Aight. Have a nice walk!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.72,0:03:17.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're off!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.88,0:03:18.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.80,0:03:20.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right, nice walk to everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.97,0:03:27.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.80,0:03:28.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, ladies!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.09,0:03:30.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.19,0:03:33.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I've been told a Doctor lives\Nsomewhere here. Know anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.88,0:03:36.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor Deighton can see you\Nin the tent over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.98,0:03:39.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In that tent, then?\NWell, that's a godsend
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.47,0:03:40.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.18,0:03:44.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.51,0:03:45.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.38,0:03:47.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Say, sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.81,0:03:50.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The bottle doctor just gave you - what's it for?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.63,0:03:52.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Alcohol for disinfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.54,0:03:54.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it! 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.06,0:03:57.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor then waters it down in order to drink it\Ninstead of normal booze.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.90,0:04:00.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't be saying such nonsense, Kate.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.40,0:04:02.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I saw it with my own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.60,0:04:04.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then just politely forget about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.15,0:04:06.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.19,0:04:09.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell is able to walk again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.89,0:04:11.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, we're approaching the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.90,0:04:13.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Shut it! I can see that much myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.30,0:04:17.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Dr. Deighton, his waist healed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.60,0:04:20.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He may be a drunkard,\Nbut he's also an excellent doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.75,0:04:21.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That may be so, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.09,0:04:24.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, careful, careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.38,0:04:26.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Shut it! Idiots must keep silent!
Comment: 0,0:04:27.30,0:04:28.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.18,0:04:31.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch! Ouch! Ouch! Ouch! Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.92,0:04:40.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch! Ouch! Ouch! Ouch! Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.98,0:04:42.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.51,0:04:45.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world had happened?\NCome on, hold on to me! Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.43,0:04:46.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And... up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.22,0:04:50.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up already! So much ado over nothing! 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.00,0:04:53.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A fine house, however you look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.89,0:04:56.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Our own house stands in no comparison to this!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.99,0:04:59.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hard to believe we could really live in it ourselves. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.40,0:05:02.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you before not to bring it up anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.13,0:05:07.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, why don't you quit stopping in front of it\Nto say wistfully "a fine house," whenever we pass by? 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.00,0:05:11.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah? That was pretty brash of you,\Nyou know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.41,0:05:18.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I know exactly why dad decided to sell this prefabricated home and buy our current house instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.09,0:05:19.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Why was it, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.74,0:05:21.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I won't tell you because you'll get mad again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.26,0:05:24.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure I won't get mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.23,0:05:25.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can hardly believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.56,0:05:28.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I promise I won't get mad, so speak up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.59,0:05:30.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thing is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.69,0:05:31.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.81,0:05:34.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,On the second thought, I should stop! 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.38,0:05:53.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May! Hurry up after us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.05,0:05:54.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.50,0:06:06.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm so sorry, Marsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.50,0:06:09.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay, Lucy-May?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.26,0:06:10.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.03,0:06:13.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That was dangerous.\NThe roads here haven't been paved yet. 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.08,0:06:15.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Calling this a road is an overstatement.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.29,0:06:17.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even though they named it already.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.10,0:06:20.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In Adelaide, they give everything a name\Nbefore anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.06,0:06:25.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, they've settled on naming the town Adelaide before they even decided where to build it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.00,0:06:27.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.98,0:06:33.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I won't be looking to the sides anymore, so don't worry. \NReturn safely to your afternoon nap.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.69,0:06:38.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And what's the name of this one street?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.16,0:06:39.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Waymouth Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.67,0:06:41.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? You know already?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.70,0:06:45.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It must be that you've been coming here\Nto play in secret from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.27,0:06:46.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I know even without ever coming here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.88,0:06:50.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The street next to Currie Street\Nis Waymouth Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.09,0:06:52.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Not bad at all, Kate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.50,0:06:54.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, about what you said before...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.62,0:06:55.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Promise you won't get mad?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.93,0:06:56.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.90,0:06:59.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So why did dad decide to buy {\i1}that{\i0} house?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.99,0:07:03.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I secretly eavesdropped\Non dad's conversation with Mr. Parker.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.42,0:07:07.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,By Jove, seeing and hearing things in secret\Nis probably what you do best.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.90,0:07:09.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you say so, I probably shouldn't tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.95,0:07:12.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I won't say a word more.\NSo come on and tell me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.58,0:07:14.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Kate?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.40,0:07:17.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's cause our new house was awfully cheap!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.90,0:07:20.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's all? I could tell you that much myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.83,0:07:22.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But do you know its cost exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.60,0:07:24.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, of course I can't know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.28,0:07:26.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was a measly five pounds!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.50,0:07:27.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Five pounds?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.09,0:07:31.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And how much do you think\NMr. Pettywell paid for the prefabricated home?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.19,0:07:35.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I know we bought it\Nfor 30 pounds back in England.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.51,0:07:38.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And here, he sold it for 110 pounds!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.24,0:07:39.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,110 pounds?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.73,0:07:42.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And know what? Mr. Parker\Nalso lined his pockets on that... 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.51,0:07:43.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.78,0:07:44.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.90,0:07:48.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough. You're being way too nosy\Nin the grown-ups' affairs. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.90,0:07:51.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But just cause I heard it\Ndoesn't mean I wanted to hear it. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.62,0:07:53.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I was just taking a nap there...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.20,0:07:54.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then be so kind as to forget that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.92,0:07:57.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Children should stick to things befitting children.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.41,0:08:03.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if it would've been better if you were more\Nlike Lucy-May, only going nuts over animals. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.71,0:08:06.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? But I'm also concerned with a whole lot of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.69,0:08:10.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The population increased sharply,\Nwhich means various goods became sparse.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.53,0:08:12.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Prices also went considerably up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.11,0:08:15.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's true.\NYou even know that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.50,0:08:16.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My, that's a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.49,0:08:20.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I learned that from the conversation I overheard\Nbetween mom and Mrs. Mac.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.84,0:08:22.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. So that's where it came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.70,0:08:24.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.94,0:08:29.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's thanks to my fascination with animals\Nthat you get to drink goat milk daily.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.48,0:08:30.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You remember that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.61,0:08:32.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That was my point as well. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.61,0:08:33.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Oh no.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.21,0:08:36.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Lucy-May?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.00,0:08:41.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to give Billy\None of Sticky's babies today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.71,0:08:43.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.05,0:08:45.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Billy would probably come for it. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.40,0:08:48.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is bad. I completely forgot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.09,0:08:51.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If we're quick enough to be done with shopping,\Nwe'll be home before dusk.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.29,0:08:52.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.28,0:08:58.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I really don't wanna break my own promise...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.60,0:09:09.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, thank you for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.10,0:09:12.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And take a break from work for two or three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.64,0:09:16.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, my other hand is still alright,\Nso I can use the saw just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.47,0:09:19.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's your head that I'm most concerned about.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.09,0:09:21.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, just stay put for two or tree days, will ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.75,0:09:23.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you say so, Doctor... 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.00,0:09:28.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Morning, doc!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.58,0:09:32.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? But Kate and Lucy, while clinging to Clara,\Nwent shopping already.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.22,0:09:33.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.02,0:09:34.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... A little while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.63,0:09:35.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.10,0:09:46.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I wonder which of the babies\Nwill Lucy-May let me have.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.27,0:10:19.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Billy. You need something here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.30,0:10:22.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-uh. I came here\Nbecause of my promise with Lucy-May.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.38,0:10:23.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You couldn't find her anywhere? 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.92,0:10:25.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I was told she went shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.71,0:10:26.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.49,0:10:33.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ben, isn't there anything I could help with?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.80,0:10:35.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'd feel bad if I asked you... 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.19,0:10:37.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I ain't got anything better to do while waiting. 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.40,0:10:38.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just say how I could help!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.80,0:10:40.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right? You don't mind, do you, dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.98,0:10:44.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So you're saying you wanna work, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.50,0:10:47.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ben, let him change places with you for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.19,0:10:48.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Though I still feel bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.91,0:10:50.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing to feel bad about!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.91,0:10:53.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There'll come a day when Billy\Nwould also have to quit playing games. 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.69,0:10:57.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If his first desire to work had finally hatched,\Nwe let him work.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.91,0:11:02.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, we load this dirt onto a sled,\Nso as to carry it all to the pit over there. 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.28,0:11:03.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.61,0:11:10.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're about the same age\Nas our Kate, aren't you, Billy?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.19,0:11:11.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.07,0:11:17.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And Kate had only mastered the art of chatter,\Nwithout ever being of any use to us. 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.57,0:11:20.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This here must be the King William Street, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.21,0:11:21.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.24,0:11:23.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We made it to Adelaide's central street.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.50,0:11:34.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it Mr. Bernard?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.10,0:11:35.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My, you're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.32,0:11:37.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.19,0:11:39.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where could you three be heading to?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.87,0:11:41.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're going shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.11,0:11:42.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If so, good luck with that. 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.52,0:11:43.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bernard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.71,0:11:44.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.42,0:11:47.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is it okay for you to be taking a stroll\Nduring your working hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.18,0:11:50.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh-eh? No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.74,0:11:52.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You think I'm just taking a stroll here? 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.58,0:11:56.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm returning from Governor-General's residence,\Nto where I've delivered Colonel Light's report.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.72,0:11:58.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... We're so sorry, Mr. Bernard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.88,0:12:01.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate! Your audacity really knows no bounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.90,0:12:06.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You need to moderate what you're saying about the grown-ups' affairs that you don't yet fully understand. 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.74,0:12:07.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.10,0:12:20.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, come see it! Come on! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.90,0:12:28.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Clara, what kind of store is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.50,0:12:30.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Seems to be a store for lamps and furniture.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.92,0:12:32.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.13,0:12:34.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what they have in that one!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.27,0:12:39.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sister, come quickly!\NYou should see it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.96,0:12:40.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.69,0:12:45.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sis, what about this store?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.51,0:12:47.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In here, they sell clothes and fabric.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.71,0:12:48.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.21,0:12:57.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That was Mrs. Pettywell!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.51,0:12:59.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe she came to order\Na new dress tailored for her? 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.79,0:13:01.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you saw it? Saw it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.39,0:13:02.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Saw what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.02,0:13:04.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I saw it just now, when they opened\Nthe door wide for her!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.93,0:13:05.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.89,0:13:07.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate, you didn't see it either?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.70,0:13:09.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't see anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.02,0:13:11.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I was busy looking at Mrs. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.29,0:13:13.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then you should definitely\Ncome peek at it through here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.42,0:13:16.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.30,0:13:17.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.29,0:13:20.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it's about time we left, you two.\NThat's enough distractions for one day. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.40,0:13:22.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, what did you see there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.31,0:13:23.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was a wedding dress! 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.78,0:13:24.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.71,0:13:25.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.03,0:13:27.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But we can't see it\Nunless the door opens again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.55,0:13:28.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's open it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.32,0:13:28.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.01,0:13:30.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'll enter in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.80,0:13:32.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure you don't mind, sis?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.48,0:13:33.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see why I should mind. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.93,0:13:36.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After all, they might have something\Nthat we happen to need, too. 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.49,0:14:07.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Ah, welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.00,0:14:14.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to have a dress\Ntailored for you, m'lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.70,0:14:16.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh... Yes...
Comment: 0,0:14:16.39,0:14:17.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.06,0:14:18.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.60,0:14:21.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, that would be the dress for you, won't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.55,0:14:24.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.51,0:14:25.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.41,0:14:27.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How much is this wedding dress?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.65,0:14:28.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.09,0:14:28.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.55,0:14:32.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, this one? This is not for sale, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.48,0:14:34.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.12,0:14:37.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're using this dress\Nas a sort of eye-catcher for the shop. 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.29,0:14:39.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But if you could sell it hypothetically,\Nhow much would it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.90,0:14:41.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,M'lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.01,0:14:46.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you happen to need a wedding dress,\NI'd be happy to make one for you in to time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.90,0:14:48.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm already in love with this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.09,0:14:51.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt, it's a marvelous dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.03,0:14:54.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But that's also why, like I said before,\Nselling it is out of question.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.58,0:15:02.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But so be it, if it happens to fit your body perfectly,\NI could lend it to you, if you'd like it. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.01,0:15:03.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.30,0:15:04.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Telling lies is not in my habit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.00,0:15:09.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,However, only a person lean enough\Nwould be able to wear this bridal gown. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.19,0:15:11.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to try it on, m'lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.34,0:15:13.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Yes.
Comment: 0,0:15:13.58,0:15:14.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.69,0:15:21.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... But I'm afraid\NI don't have any time for it today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.38,0:15:22.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So I'd do it later. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.60,0:15:23.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.48,0:15:24.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye!
Comment: 0,0:15:25.22,0:15:26.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.41,0:15:31.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's with that girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.81,0:15:36.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sister! Walk slower, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.89,0:15:48.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Say, sis, why'd you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.40,0:15:49.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I was too embarrassed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.75,0:15:50.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.19,0:15:55.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't really need a wedding dress.\NBut I nearly ended up ordering one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.38,0:15:58.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Still, when I have enough time,\NI'll come to take a closer look at that dress. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.11,0:16:00.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was a really pretty one!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.66,0:16:03.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you put it on, I'm sure\Nyou'll make for a gorgeous bride!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.10,0:16:05.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.20,0:16:08.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sis, you've not forgotten John, after all, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.73,0:16:10.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, Kate! You're being impudent again!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.44,0:16:14.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But hey - why else would you need\Nto take a closer look at that wedding dress?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.12,0:16:17.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was a stunning dress,\Nanyone could see that! 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.19,0:16:20.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It's just as you said, Lucy-May.\NLet's go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.81,0:16:23.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?\NWanna give it another glance?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.62,0:16:26.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We went right past the grocery store.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.58,0:16:29.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was right there, just one house away\Nfrom the tailor's shop. 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.91,0:16:32.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We've come quite a way from it, then. 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.69,0:16:34.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.32,0:16:49.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Aside from that, only the flour.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.08,0:16:50.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Flour, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.59,0:16:53.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Your flour.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.01,0:16:55.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's all we can get? 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.78,0:16:57.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's a rather small bag indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.82,0:17:00.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought,\Nthe flour turned out to be expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.31,0:17:01.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Anything else you need?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.89,0:17:04.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right. I almost forgot\NI also need alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.71,0:17:06.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have any alcohol here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.88,0:17:08.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But you have spirits, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.80,0:17:11.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What you need is medical alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.04,0:17:13.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, where can we find a pharmacist? 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.12,0:17:14.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.06,0:17:14.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.39,0:17:19.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My son trades in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.09,0:17:25.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please fill it with alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.34,0:17:26.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.21,0:17:32.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow, it feels like my load\Nis the most burdensome. 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.60,0:17:33.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.71,0:17:36.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'd rather not carry something like salted meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.61,0:17:39.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But you were the one who said\N"I'll carry it myself," weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.97,0:17:44.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's true. I said I wanna carry some package\Nthat's relatively small but still heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.54,0:17:45.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it smells a lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.91,0:17:47.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well that's 'cause it's meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.46,0:17:50.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Since it's been pickled in salt,\Nit wasn't supposed to putrefy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.38,0:17:54.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.68,0:17:59.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! We ran into Mr. Bernard again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.29,0:18:01.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.90,0:18:06.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the public office\Nwhere Mr. Bernard works?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.35,0:18:07.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.61,0:18:13.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,"Adelaide Times." A newspaper, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.29,0:18:21.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll leave the rest to you, Mr. Cope.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.12,0:18:21.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.58,0:18:29.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Adelaide even has its own newspaper now?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.14,0:18:30.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.20,0:18:34.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Clara, do you encourage your father\Nto read newspapers? 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.55,0:18:35.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.59,0:18:39.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The one running the Adelaide Times is Mr. Cope,\Nquite a gifted fellow. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.65,0:18:41.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,His articles are always 100% accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.60,0:18:43.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do they publish it daily?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.16,0:18:44.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,On Sunday, they have a day off.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.95,0:18:50.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I never had any idea something article-worthy can happen in a place so sparsely populated on a daily basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.08,0:18:51.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's not exactly like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.35,0:18:53.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Let me carry that bag for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.10,0:18:54.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I can handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.27,0:18:55.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No need to be so modest. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.11,0:18:56.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.51,0:19:00.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You won't be returning to your office?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.55,0:19:02.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I've finished my work for today. 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.69,0:19:07.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Darling, are these the ones?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.17,0:19:08.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, lemme see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.70,0:19:18.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hope they grow well here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.19,0:19:20.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. They should do perfectly fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.44,0:19:23.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be really delighted if we manage to gather\Nspinach and carrots soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.95,0:19:28.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,England and Australia have polar opposite climates\Nand soil qualities, so I can't know for sure. 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.28,0:19:32.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I think it'll only became clear after we\Nplant the seeds and let them fully develop.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.81,0:19:39.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,As for this radish, it sprouted way sooner\Nthan back in England and is already big enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.88,0:19:42.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm. I also feel like the growth\Nis significantly faster here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.79,0:19:46.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, we'll try planting carrots and spinach\Nto see how they would fare.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.61,0:19:50.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This tiny vegetable garden would provide\Nfor perfect testing ground. 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.47,0:19:54.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The thought of it becoming something else than that\Nis unbearable to me. 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.66,0:19:57.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,By Jove, when in the world\Nare they going to give us any proper land? 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.99,0:20:01.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ben! Billy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.31,0:20:03.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Need a bit of helping hand here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.93,0:20:07.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This hole is now so deep\NI can no longer get out on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.31,0:20:10.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Raise me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.64,0:20:12.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh. And... up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.90,0:20:18.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks. I'll go put together a rope ladder now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.60,0:20:22.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Also, I need to reinforce the walls with wood\Nso that the soil around it remains in place. 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.16,0:20:25.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, I can get in the hole\Ninstead of you and keep digging.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.51,0:20:29.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Digging should be easy now, as the ground\Nis already quite damp and soft down there. 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.20,0:20:31.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Billy, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.89,0:20:34.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose Lucy-May and others\Nshould be returning soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.98,0:20:39.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thought so. Dad! Once Lucy-May gives me the goat,\NI can return home, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.65,0:20:40.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.45,0:20:49.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Alley-hop!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.85,0:20:52.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch! Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.38,0:21:00.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's wet. How come there water here, amidst earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.14,0:21:07.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're late, Lucy-May!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.42,0:21:25.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Your dad hired Mr. Jamling to help him fix the house\Nand dig the water well, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.39,0:21:30.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Looking at it from outside, I couldn't help thinking\Nit probably cost him a small fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.81,0:21:34.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's because he got some insane money\Nfrom selling our prefabricated home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.16,0:21:35.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? I thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.73,0:21:38.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I guess, I've been worrying over nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.37,0:21:41.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how that prefabricated home\Nlooks from inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.10,0:21:42.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,but its exterior is outright glorious.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.86,0:21:44.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's just as comfortable on the inside, I suppose. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.90,0:21:49.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't anyone follow Mr. Popple's example\Nto also bring with them that sort of prefabricated home?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.62,0:21:52.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That looks like an easy way to start a comfortable life. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.08,0:21:56.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I've had enough of those talks\Nabout the prefabricated home... 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.25,0:21:58.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Make an effort and walk faster, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.21,0:21:59.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm tired!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.69,0:22:00.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.79,0:22:02.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a break for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.35,0:22:03.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.73,0:22:06.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?\NWe're still a long way from home. 
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.52,0:22:08.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that why we should take a break?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.20,0:22:11.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't your bag a bit heavy for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.07,0:22:12.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.29,0:22:13.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Give it here. I'll carry it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.72,0:22:15.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yay!
Comment: 0,0:22:15.90,0:22:16.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.91,0:22:18.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bernard, I love you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.02,0:22:21.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.48,0:22:24.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? That too?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.15,0:22:27.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You can't do that!\NThere's salted meat in that package.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.42,0:22:29.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The scent will spread to Mr. Bernard. 
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.76,0:22:31.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, you carry it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.86,0:22:35.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I took you with me because you promised\Nto carry your bags properly until the end! 
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.85,0:22:38.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's keep going, Mr. Bernard.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.29,0:22:42.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're a miser sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.38,0:22:50.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Here, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.61,0:22:52.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, thanks a bunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.80,0:23:04.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... Billy had been waiting all day!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.35,0:23:06.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you make a promise with him or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.91,0:23:08.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I did!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.99,0:23:19.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, today we're parting with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.91,0:23:26.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Because Lucy-May had already promised it,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.80,0:23:31.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,she insisted obstinately\Non delivering the goatling to Billy before dark. 
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.61,0:23:33.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.40,0:23:37.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna go too!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.09,0:23:53.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hope that before long this goatling would be able\Nto provide Billy's family with plenty of milk, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.62,0:24:06.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When we went into the woods to look for a koala,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.42,0:24:11.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,we found instead a dingo, about to attack some sheep.\NLook out! We need to save them quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.29,0:24:14.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Next on Lucy-May of the Southern Rainbow:\N"Water in the Well".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.61,0:24:15.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
